ZH: 他总是敷衍塞责地应付工作。
EN: He always handles his work in a perfunctory manner.

ZH: 她对这个项目的进展只是敷衍塞责地交代了几句。
EN: She just briefly explained the progress of the project in a perfunctory way.

ZH: 我们希望领导不要只是敷衍塞责地提出批评。
EN: We hope that the leaders do not just make perfunctory criticisms.

ZH: 他太过敷衍塞责，导致整个团队的工作都出了问题。
EN: His perfunctory attitude caused problems for the entire team's work.

ZH: 这次会议上，部长对大家提出的问题只是敷衍塞责地回答。
EN: During the meeting, the minister just made perfunctory responses to the questions raised by everyone.

ZH: 我们不想看到领导只是敷衍塞责地处理这个严重的问题。
EN: We do not want to see the leaders perfunctorily deal with this serious issue.

ZH: 她总是敷衍塞责地完成任务，从来不认真对待。
EN: She always completes tasks in a perfunctory manner and never takes them seriously.

ZH: 领导对员工的问题只是敷衍塞责地推卸责任。
EN: The leader just shirks responsibility by perfunctorily addressing the employee's concerns.

ZH: 他对客户的投诉只能敷衍塞责地回答一些问题。
EN: He can only give perfunctory responses to customer complaints.

ZH: 我们应该认真对待工作，不要敷衍塞责。
EN: We should take our work seriously and not be perfunctory.

ZH: 她对这个任务的态度太过敷衍塞责了。
EN: Her attitude towards this task is too perfunctory.

ZH: 领导总是敷衍塞责，不解决实质问题。
EN: The leader always shirks responsibility and does not address the real issues.

ZH: 我不喜欢别人敷衍塞责地回答我的问题。
EN: I don't like it when others answer my questions perfunctorily.

ZH: 他总是敷衍塞责地对待学习，从不认真学习。
EN: He always treats studying perfunctorily and never studies seriously.

ZH: 领导对这个计划的提议只是敷衍塞责地批准了。
EN: The leader just perfunctorily approved the proposal for this plan.

ZH: 他完全是敷衍塞责地对待自己的职责。
EN: He completely shirks his responsibilities in a perfunctory manner.

ZH: 我不要任何人敷衍塞责地处理这个重要的项目。
EN: I don't want anyone to handle this important project perfunctorily.

ZH: 领导总是敷衍塞责地应付工作，这不是好的态度。
EN: The leader always perfunctorily deals with work, which is not a good attitude.

